What is IAM policy evaluation logic?
IAM policy evaluation logic is the process AWS uses to determine whether a request to access a resource is allowed or denied
based on the policies attached to the IAM identities (users, groups, roles) and resource-based policies.
The evaluation follows these steps:
1. By default, all requests are denied.
2. AWS evaluates all applicable policies (identity-based and resource-based) for the request.
3. If any policy explicitly denies the request, the request is denied.
4. If there are no explicit denies and at least one policy explicitly allows the request, the request is allowed.
5. If there are no explicit allows or denies, the request remains denied by default.
Conditions specified in policies are also evaluated during this process, and they can further refine the access
permissions based on factors such as time of day, IP address, or multi-factor authentication (MFA) status.
This evaluation logic ensures that access control is enforced consistently and securely across AWS resources.
